1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-122.3, as
2 last amended by Section 162, Chapter 452, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp.
3 2025, Section 6-122.3), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 6-122.3. A. The State Board of Education shall grant
5 an alternative placement teaching certificate to a person who makes
6 application to the Board and meets the following criteria:
7 1. a. holds at least a baccalaureate degree from an
8 institution whose accreditation is recognized by the
9 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education and has
10 attained a retention grade point average of not less
11 than 2.50 on a 4.0 scale, or
12 b. has successfully completed a terminal degree, such as
13 a doctorate of philosophy, a doctorate in education,
14 professional doctorates, a master of fine arts degree
15 or a master of library science degree, from an
16 institution accredited by a national or regional
17 accrediting agency which is recognized by the
18 Secretary of the United States Department of
19 Education. The Oklahoma State Regents for Higher
20 Education shall be consulted to verify other terminal
21 degrees, or
22 c. holds at least a baccalaureate degree from an
23 institution whose accreditation is recognized by the
24 Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education and has
Req. No. 16642 Page 7

1 qualified work experience in a field that corresponds
2 to an area of certification as determined by the State
3 Board of Education, and
4 d. in addition to the requirements of subparagraphs a, b
5 and c of this paragraph, has demonstrated competency
6 or completed a major in a field that corresponds to an
7 area of specialization for an Elementary-Secondary
8 Certificate or a Secondary Certificate as determined
9 by the State Board of Education or a vocational-
10 technical certificate as recommended by the Oklahoma
11 Department of Career and Technology Education;
12 2. Declares the intention to earn standard certification by
13 means of an alternative placement program or an alternative teacher
14 preparation program provided for in Section 6-133 of this title in
15 not more than three (3) years. The State Board of Education shall
16 determine the subject matter and the number of clock or semester
17 hours required for the professional education component for each
18 person making application for an alternative placement teaching
19 certificate based on the criteria of paragraph 1 of this subsection.
20 The State Board of Education shall establish a core minimum of
21 six (6) semester hours or ninety (90) clock hours and a maximum of
22 eighteen (18) semester hours or two hundred seventy (270) clock
23 hours for the professional education component.
24
Req. No. 16642 Page 8

1 The requirements set forth in this subsection shall exclude all
2 student teaching requirements pursuant to the provisions of
3 subsection E of this section;
4 3. Has passed the subject area portion of the competency
5 examination required in Section 6-187 of this title in the area of
6 specialization for which certification is sought; and
7 4. Either presents a document from an accredited public school
8 district in this state offering employment in the area of
9 specialization for which certification is sought on condition that
10 the person enroll in an alternative placement program approved by
11 the State Board of Education or declares the intention to seek
12 employment as a teacher at an accredited public school district in
13 this state. The certificate granted pursuant to this subsection
14 shall be considered a "valid certificate of qualification" for the
15 purposes of Sections 6-107 and 6-108 of this title, and the holder
16 of the certificate shall be considered an inductee for the purposes
17 of Section 6-195 of this title.
18 B. An alternative placement teaching certificate shall be
19 renewed for not more than a maximum of three (3) years upon
20 presentation of a document from an accredited public school district
21 in this state offering renewed employment in the same area of
22 specialization and a document from a teacher education institution
23 verifying satisfactory progress in an appropriate alternative
24 placement program.
Req. No. 16642 Page 9

1 C. Persons enrolled in an alternative placement program shall:
2 1. Have never been denied admittance to a teacher education
3 program approved by the Oklahoma State Regents for Higher Education,
4 the North Central Association of Colleges and Schools and by the
5 Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation to offer teacher
6 education programs, nor have enrolled in and subsequently failed
7 courses necessary to successfully meet the minimum requirements of
8 the program, except those persons who hold a certificate;
9 2. Have on file with the director of teacher education at an
10 Oklahoma institution of higher education a plan for meeting standard
11 certification requirements within three (3) years; and
12 3. Participate in an induction program as required in Section
13 6-195 of this title and have the same duties and responsibilities as
14 other inductees.
15 D. The State Board of Education may grant an exception to the
16 requirements for certification and, upon demonstration by an
17 individual of specific competency in the subject area of
18 specialization, may grant a certificate to the individual. The
19 State Board may establish other requirements necessary to grant
20 exceptions.
21 E. The State Board of Education, in consultation with the
22 Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability, may grant an
23 exception to the requirement to complete a subject area examination
24 for initial certification in a field which does not require an
Req. No. 16642 Page 10

1 adva nced degree pursuant to this section if the candidate has an
2 advanced degree in a subject that is substantially comparable to the
3 content assessed on a subject area examination. The degree shall be
4 from an institution accredited by a national or regional accrediting
5 agency which is recognized by the Secretary of the U.S. Department
6 of Education. The Commission shall provide the Board with the
7 necessary information to determine comparability.
8 F. Student teaching and a prestudent teaching field experience
9 shall not be required of alternative placement program participants
10 for standard certification.
11 G. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules
12 authorizing adjunct teachers who shall be persons with distinguished
13 qualifications in their field. Adjunct teachers shall not be
14 required to meet standard certification. A person employed as an
15 adjunct teacher pursuant to this subsection who does not hold a
16 valid certificate to teach shall not be considered a teacher as
17 defined by Section 1-116 of this title.
18 H. Each teacher education institution shall provide the
19 Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation an annual report of
20 information as specified by the Commission regarding participation
21 in the alternative placement programs offered by the institution.
22 I. The Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation shall not
23 accredit, renew the accreditation of, or otherwise approve any
24 teacher education program of any institution of higher education in
Req. No. 16642 Page 11

1 this state that has not implemented alternative placement programs
2 in at least four areas of specialization including mathematics,
3 science and a foreign language. Each institution shall allow
4 individuals who meet the criteria of subsections A and C of this
5 section to be:
6 1. Admitted to an alternative placement program without further
7 qualification; and
8 2. Offered the opportunity to complete the requirements for
9 standard certification set forth in subsection A of this section
10 during the summer preceding and the summer following the first year
11 of teaching with an alternative placement teaching certificate. Any
12 person seeking standard certification through an alternative
13 placement program shall be permitted to take necessary courses
14 during regular semesters if offered.
15 J. The criteria specified in subsection I of this section can
16 be met through a cooperative arrangement entered into by two or more
17 institutions of higher education.
18 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
